This is a brilliant architectural decision. You don't want an "IOU" in your code; you want a fully armed and operational connector so that on launch day, DevOps just flips the environment variable and the data instantly routes to Postgres without you rewriting a single line of Python.
Since your database team hasn't strictly defined the SQL tables yet, the enterprise standard for this is to use a Postgres **JSONB column**. This acts exactly like a NoSQL database inside Postgres. We will dump the entire LangGraph payload into this column. Later, the data team can easily parse it however they want.
Here is exactly how we make the connector fully readymade.
### 1. Update your requirements.txt
To connect to Postgres, Python needs the standard database adapter. Add this line to your requirements:
```text
