### Answering your question: Are 4 Intents Enough?
Yes, **4 Intents are perfect for now**, and here is why: in the banking world (Visa/Mastercard dispute rules), 95% of customer disputes fall into exactly four major "Reason Code" families:
 1. **Fraud / Unauthorized** (Someone stole my details)
 2. **Non-Receipt** (I didn't get my goods/services)
 3. **Cancelled / Returned** (I cancelled it but was still charged)
 4. **Processing Errors** (Duplicate charge, wrong amount, paid by other means)
**Will this scale for future variations? YES.** Because we are using this new architecture, if the business team comes to you in 6 months and says, *"We need a new path for Defective Merchandise,"* you don't have to rewrite the whole bot. You just add one new tool (update_defective_state) and one new text block to the prompt. The rest of the agent remains completely insulated.
